Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 1500 / 3 / 0 / 1500 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 4
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 354 / 11 / 0 / 354 / 0
Swine / 1500 / 3 / 0 / 1500 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: 4 more outbreaks were found between 9 and 10 Apr
2010. All cloven-hoofed animals within a radius of 3 km [2 mi] from the
affected premises were culled. The culling was completed on 18 Apr 2010.

Control measures
Measures applied:
- stamping out;
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- zoning;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s);
- vaccination prohibited;
- no treatment of affected animals

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Research and Quarantine
Service (NVRQS) (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / gene sequencing / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / rapid tests / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / real-time PCR / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Swine / antibody detection ELISA / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Swine / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Swine / gene sequencing / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Swine / rapid tests / 10 Apr 2010 / positive
Swine / real-time PCR / 10 Apr 2010 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

