Foot and mouth disease, Korea (Rep of)
--------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 22 Apr 2010 from Dr Kiyoon Chang, CVO &
Director, Labelling, Quarantine and Inspection Division, Food Safety &
Consumer Affairs Policy Bureau, MIFAFF (Ministry of Food, Agriculture,
Forestry and Fisheries), Gyeonggi-Do, Korea (Rep of)

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 2
Start date: 8 Apr 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 9 Apr 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Apr 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 11 Mar 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Wolgot-myeon, Gimpo-city, Kyonggi-do
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 120 / 1 / 0 / 120 / 0
Affected Population Dairy cattle

Outbreak 2: Buleun-myeon, Ganghwa-gun, Inch'on-jikhalsi
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 19 / 2 / 0 / 19 / 0
Goats / 6 / 0 / 0 / 6 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 139 / 3 / 0 / 139 / 0
Goats / 6 / 0 / 0 / 6 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.

Epidemiological comments: a farmer in Gimpo first found a suspicious case
which had anorexia and vesicles in teats and reported it to the National
Veterinary Research and Quarantine Service (NVRQS) on 19 Apr 2010. The
NVRQS affirmed that the cattle were infected with FMD virus by PCR and
ELISA on 20 Apr 2010. Not only were culled the cattle in the affected farm
but also all cloven-hoofed animals within a radius of 500 m [0.3 mi] from
the affected farm.

A farmer in Ganghwa found a suspicious case and reported it to the local
government. The NVRQS affirmed that the cattle were infected with FMD virus
by PCR and ELISA on 22 Apr 2010. Not only were culled the cattle in the
affected farm but also all cloven-hoofed animals within a radius of 500 m
[0.3 mi] from the affected farm.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Research and Quarantine
Service (NVRQS) (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 20 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 22 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 20 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 22 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / rapid tests / 20 Apr 2010 / positive
Cattle / rapid tests / 22 Apr 2010 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
